<b>Jaime G. Carbonell</b> is <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../304/287304.xml">
Alan Newell</link> Professor of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../323/5323.xml">
Computer Science</link> and the director of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../940/13511940.xml">
Language Technologies Institute</link> at <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../093/48093.xml">
Carnegie Mellon University</link></university>
. <p>

He earned his <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../904/124904.xml">
B.S.</link> degrees in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../939/22939.xml">
Physics</link> and in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../831/18831.xml">
Mathematics</link> from <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../061/19061.xml">
MIT</link> in 1975 and his <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/8775.xml">
Ph.D.</link> under Dr. <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<scientist wordnetid="110560637" confidence="0.8">
<research_worker wordnetid="110523076" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../541/1076541.xml">
Roger Schank</link></research_worker>
</scientist>
</causal_agent>
</person>
</physical_entity>
 at <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../273/34273.xml">
Yale University</link></university>
 in 1979.</p>
<p>

His interests span several areas of <link>
Artificial Intelligence</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../008/252008.xml">
Language technologies</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../488/233488.xml">
Machine Learning</link>. In particular, his research is focused on areas such as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../439/318439.xml">
text mining</link> (extraction, categorization, novelty detection) and in new theoretical frameworks such as a unified utility-based theory bridging <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
information retrieval</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../199/637199.xml">
summarization</link>, free-text <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../030/360030.xml">
question-answering</link> and related tasks.  He also works on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../980/19980.xml">
Machine Translation</link>, both high-accuracy knowledge-based MT and machine learning for <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../491/4558491.xml">
corpus-based MT</link> (such as generalized <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../043/54043.xml">
example-based MT</link>).</p>


